text.section:
The plan of operation shall:
establish procedures for the performance of the powers and duties of the Corporation specified in § 9-306 of this subtitle;
establish procedures for handling the assets of the Corporation;
establish the amounts to be reimbursed and the method of reimbursing members of the Board of Directors under § 9-305 of this subtitle;
establish procedures for filing claims with the Corporation;
establish acceptable forms of proof of covered claims;
establish regular places and times for meetings of the Board of Directors;
establish procedures for keeping records of the financial transactions of the Corporation, its agents, and the Board of Directors;
provide that a member insurer that is aggrieved by a final action or decision of the Corporation may appeal to the Commissioner within 30 days after the action or decision; and
contain any additional provisions necessary or proper to perform the powers and duties of the Corporation.
